{"questionId":"22271563","questionHtml":"<p>Write down an integral that represents this volume.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></msubsup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>dx</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></msubsup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; (or equivalent)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for integral with correct limits in the correct places, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for completely correct expression;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;must be included. Condone a correct answer presented as two integrals, despite the demand of the question:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>0</mn></msubsup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></msubsup><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"22271563","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.10bi","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down an integral that represents this volume.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.12—Areas under a curve onto x or y axis. Volumes of revolution about x and y"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}